Title: Middle of the road
Definition: 1. Describing an option that is neither the most nor the least expensive.

Title: up in the air
Definition: To be uncertain or subject to change.

Title: go to bat
Definition: To act in support of one.

Title: cooking something up
Definition: A noun or pronoun can be used between "cook" and "up."

Title: cherry picking
Definition: 1. To choose something very carefully to ensure that the best option is chosen, perhaps through means that provide one an unfair advantage or from a selection that others do not have ready access to.

Title: hot to trot
Definition: 1. Eager or impatient to do something.

Title: cutting your teeth on something
Definition: To gain experience with something, especially at a young age (when one's teeth would be coming in).
